  "text": "In order to account for the losses due to electron scattering in doped graphene, adapting the Mermin procedure, the modified bare density correlation function can be written as [CITATION_1] Πγ(q, w) = (1 + iγ/w)Π(q, w + iγ) 1 + (iγ/w)Π(q, w + iγ)/Π(q, 0)",
